  <a href="/users/alea-iactaest" title="View user profile."><img src="/sites/all/themes/newsflash/images/bagicon.png" alt="Alea Iactaest&#039;s picture" title="Alea Iactaest&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>You might want to reconsider your line, "I've never seen anything drop in price as demand skyrockets".</p>
<p>It happens in manufacturing all the time (think personal computers).</p>
<p>It happens as a result of trade when goods can be moved from a point of production to a point of consumption (think spice trade in Europe).</p>
<p>It can also happen with commodities as new sources of supply are discovered for a previously scarce material.</p>
<p>All manipulation, I'm sure.</p>

