    <p>I'm sure once we hit the Freegold price of $55k/oz we'll see some ingenuity.</p>
<p>The oceans reportedly hold enough gold particles that "each person on Earth could have nine  pounds of the precious metal."<br /><a href="http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/gold.html" title="http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/gold.html" rel="nofollow">http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/gold.html</a></p>
<p>Near Earth Objects (aka asteroids and comets) likely will be targeted for mining.<br /><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/nasa-teams-asteroid-mining-company-crowdsource-space-rock-210938856.html" title="http://news.yahoo.com/nasa-teams-asteroid-mining-company-crowdsource-space-rock-210938856.html" rel="nofollow">http://news.yahoo.com/nasa-teams-asteroid-mining-company-crowdsource-spa...</a></p>

